'''MIOS''' or '''Meter Inter Operability Solution'''<ref>[https://www.zaubacorp.com/trademark/MIOS-METER-INTER-OPERABILITY-SOLUTION/825676 Trademark : MIOS (METER INTER OPERABILITY SOLUTION) Trademark Applicant : Indian Electrical And Electronics Manufacturers Association. Application Date :  2009-03-18], Applicant Address :  501, KAKAD CHAMBERS, 132, DR. ANNIE BESANT ROAD, WORLI, MUMBAI-400 018, Zauba Corp</ref> is a specification for interoperability of electric meters for remote meter reading applications in India proposed by [[Indian Electrical and Electronics Manufacturers Association|IEEMA]] in 2008.<ref>[http://www.srldc.org/var/ftp/comml/weeklysemdata/srldc%20fees/power%20system%20overview/vol4_scada,ems,IT/4Metering_rp/Further%20Reading%20Material/HLC.pdf Report of High Level Committee on Standardization of Meter Protocol Central Electricity Authority], New Delhi, December 2008, Government of India Ministry of Power</ref><ref>[https://www.metering.com/ieema-presents-meter-solution-to-indian-systems-integrators/ IEEMA presents meter solution to Indian systems integrators], 10 March 2008, Metering.com</ref><ref>[http://www.ieema.org INDIAN ELECTRICAL & ELECTRONICS MANUFACTURERS’ ASSOCIATION (IEEMA)]</ref> and is developed and maintained by Metering India which is a group of Meter Manufacturers.<ref>[http://www.kalkitech.com/download/12/ MIOS and DLMS Integration for AMI] Kalkitech</ref><ref>[http://wiki.openelectrical.org/index.php?title=Automatic_Meter_Reading Automatic Meter Reading:MIOS System Overview], Open Electrical</ref><ref>[http://www.indiacoreevents.in/bulletin/papers-amr/Madhur-Kr-Srivastava-Interoperability-Solution-for-Energy-Meter.ppt “Interoperability Solution for Energy Meter”], Mr Surendra Jhalora, Convenor- MIOS, Technical Committee, IEEMA- Presented by Mr Madhur Kumar Srivastava</ref>

