{{Infobox scientist |name = Volker Quaschning |image = Volker Quaschning2 2013.jpg |image_size = |caption = Volker Quaschning |birth_date = {{birth year and age|1969}} |birth_place = [[Leonberg]], [[Germany]] |nationality = [[Germany|German]] |field = [[Electrical engineering]], [[Renewable energy]] |work_institution = [[Hochschule für Technik und Wirtschaft Berlin]] |alma_mater = [[Karlsruhe Institute of Technology]] }}
'''Volker Quaschning''' (born 1969) is a [[Germans|German]] [[engineer]] and [[professor]] of [[renewable Energy|renewable energy systems]] at the [[Hochschule für Technik und Wirtschaft Berlin]], Germany.
== Life == Quaschning studied [[electrical engineering]] at [[Karlsruhe Institute of Technology]], then wrote his [[PhD]] on [[photovoltaics]] at the [[Technische Universität Berlin]]. After obtaining his [[habilitation]] on [[low-carbon power]] system scenarios for Germany, he worked for the [[German Aerospace Center]] in [[Almeria]], Spain and lead research into [[concentrated solar power]]. In 2004, Quaschning was appointed professor of renewable energy systems at the [[Hochschule für Technik und Wirtschaft Berlin]].<ref> {{cite web | title = Vita — Prof. Dr. Volker Quaschning | url = http://www.volker-quaschning.de/about/vita-tabelle_e/index.php | access-date = 2016-06-23 }}</ref>
Quaschning is the author of several books, including the scientific [[textbook]] ''Regenerative Energiesystems'' (Renewable energy systems), first published in 1998. In 2015, the ninth edition of this book was released. The book has been translated in [[English language|English]], [[Arabian language|Arabian]], and [[Russian language|Russian]] and a translation to the [[Kazakh language]] is in progress.<ref> {{cite web | url = http://www.volker-quaschning.de/publis/regen/index.php | title = Regenerative Energiesystems — 9. Auflage 2015 | trans-title = Renewable energy systems — 9th edition 2015 | language = German | access-date = 2016-06-23 }}</ref> According to Panos Konstantin, the book is "highly recommendable".<ref> {{cite book | first = Panos | last = Konstantin | title = Praxisbuch Energiewirtschaft: Energieumwandlung, -transport und -beschaffung im liberalisierten Markt | trans-title = Praxisbuch energy economy: energy conversion, transport and procurement in the liberalized market | language = German | year = 2009 | publisher = Springer-Verlag | place = Heidelberg, Germany | isbn = 978-3-642-37264-3 | quote = "sehr empfehlenswert" }}</ref>{{rp|312}} In 2016, an updated second edition in English was published.<ref> {{cite web | url = http://www.volker-quaschning.de/publis/regen_e/index.php | title = Understanding renewable energy systems — 2nd edition 2016 | access-date = 2016-06-23 }}</ref>
== Books == * ''Understanding Renewable Energy Systems''. Earthscan, London, 2nd edition 2016, {{ISBN|978-113878-196-2}}. * ''Regenerative Energiesysteme.'' Hanser, Munich, 9th edition 2015, {{ISBN|978-3-446-44267-2}}. * ''Erneuerbare Energien und Klimaschutz.'' Hanser, Munich, 3rd edition 2013, {{ISBN|978-3-446-43809-5}}. * ''Obnovitelné zdroje energií'', Grada Publishing Prague, 2010, {{ISBN|978-80-247-3250-3}}. * ''Mülltrenner, Müsliesser und Klimaschützer.'' Hanser, Munich, 2010, {{ISBN|978-3-446-42261-2}}. * ''Renewable Energy and Climate Change.'' John Wiley & Sons Ltd, Chichester, 2010, {{ISBN|978-0-470-74707-0}}. * ''Systemtechnik einer klimaverträglichen Elektrizitätsversorgung in Deutschland für das 21. Jahrhundert''. VDI-Verlag 2000, {{ISBN|978-3-18-343706-1}}, [http://www.volker-quaschning.de/downloads/Klima2000.pdf Online]. * ''Simulation der Abschattungsverluste bei solarelektrischen Systemen''. Phd Berlin 1996.
